records.addlTxt:
Statements made as to sentencing by State, Defense and Defendant.

Defendant sentenced to serve THREE (3) DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for THREE (3) days time served.  TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court ordered Defendant to pay ALL applicable costs, fees and surcharges by 11-30-2016 or Civil Judgment to be entered WITH Tax Intercept.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Post-conviction Relief.

Defendant Nathaneal C Patterson in court with attorney Rosemary Reyes Cuevas.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

State reports that Defendant has picked up a new case in Milwaukee County AND in Waukesha County.  The defendant is not in compliance with the terms of the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  Based upon the defendant's non-compliance, the court revoked the Deferred Prosecution Agreement; proceedings reinstated.  Court orders entry of judgment of conviction.

Attorney Rosemary Reyes Cuevas in court.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Defense advises the Court that the Defendant is in custody.  Matter is to be staffed THIS WEEK.  Court ISSUES and STAYS a Bench Warrant.  Review hearing scheduled for November 30, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Nathaneal C Patterson in court with attorney Rosemary Reyes Cuevas.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   The parties have agreed to a deferred judgment agreement.
The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, pled GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgment of Conviction.  The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the case transferred to Judge aSHLEY, Branch 33 for a Review Hearing.  Review hearing scheduled for November 9, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Nathaneal C Patterson in court with attorney Rosemary Reyes Cuevas.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. For reasons stated on the record, the Court granted the defense request for a deferred prosecution agreement hearing. Case adjourned to Branch 23. All parties are notified that effective September 14, 2015 this case will be assigned to Judge Michelle Ackerman Havas, Branch 45, in Room 515 of the Courthouse due to the rotation of Judge Grady in Branch 23.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for September 17, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Nathaneal C Patterson in court with attorney James D. Rael.  Defendant Nathaneal C Patterson in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Grady, Branch 23.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for September 3, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant Nathaneal C Patterson not in court.  James C. Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued.  Court ordered any bail posted to be forfeited.  State's motion for Judgment of Bond Forfeiture 30 days after notification from the Clerk of Circuit Court's Office is granted by the Court.  Court makes finding that there is no possible victim identified, therefore, recompense is not an issue.
SUMMONS MAILED. DEFENDANT ORDERED INTO ROOM 221 SAFETY BUILDING ON 07-06-2015 at 01:30pm
